{"name": "rnc2rng", "metadata": {"name": "rnc2rng", "version": "2.7.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Text Processing :: Markup :: XML"], "home_page": "https://github.com/djc/rnc2rng", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["rply"], "summary": "RELAX NG Compact to regular syntax conversion library", "upload_time": 1711714684}, "documentation": ["# RELAX NG Compact to RELAX NG conversion library\n\n```{image} https://github.com/djc/rnc2rng/workflows/CI/badge.svg\n:target: https://github.com/djc/rnc2rng/actions?query=workflow%3ACI\n```\n\n```{image} https://coveralls.io/repos/djc/rnc2rng/badge.svg?branch=master&service=github\n:target: https://coveralls.io/github/djc/rnc2rng?branch=master\n```\n\nConverts RELAX NG schemata in Compact syntax (`rnc`) to the equivalent schema\nin the XML-based default RELAX NG syntax. Dependencies:\n\n- Python 3.x (tested with 3.7, 3.8, 3.9)\n- [rply]\n\nFeedback welcome on [GitHub]. Please consider funding continued maintenance of this\nproject through [Patreon] or [GitHub Sponsors].\n\n## History\n\nrnc2rng was originally written by [David Mertz] in 2003 and published as part\nof a collection of files around RELAX NG [on his site] into the Public Domain.\n[Hartmut Goebel] published it as a package on PyPI to make it easier to access.\nIt was mirrored on GitHub by [Dustin J. Mitchell] in 2010 after he fixed some\nbugs. [Timmy Zhu] forked his repository and contributed further enhancements.\nRecently, I (Dirkjan Ochtman) was interested in playing with RELAX NG Compact\nand started making further updates. I asked Hartmut for maintainership on PyPI\nand received it. While I cannot promise many updates, I should be responsive to\nbug reports and (especially!) pull requests.\n\n## How to install\n\nThe usual should work:\n\n```shell\n$ sudo pip install .\n```\n\n## Getting started\n\n```shell\n$ python -m rnc2rng test.rnc > test.rng\n```\n\n## License\n\nAll of the code is released under MIT License.\n\n[david mertz]: http://www.gnosis.cx/publish/\n[dustin j. mitchell]: http://code.v.igoro.us/\n[github]: https://github.com/djc/rnc2rng\n[github sponsors]: https://github.com/sponsors/djc\n[hartmut goebel]: http://www.goebel-consult.de/\n[on his site]: http://www.gnosis.cx/download/relax/\n[patreon]: https://patreon.com/dochtman\n[rply]: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/rply\n[timmy zhu]: https://github.com/nattofriends\n"], "modules": [{"name": "rnc2rng.rnctree", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python", "Compatibility API for rnc2rng 1.0"], "functions": [{"name": "rnc2rng.rnctree.token_list", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rnc2rng.rnctree.make_nodetree", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tokens", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "rnc2rng.rnctree.Tree", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "rnc2rng.rnctree.Tree.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rnc2rng.rnctree.Tree.toxml", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "rnc2rng", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "rnc2rng.load", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rnc2rng.loads", "as